    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <head>No. 321.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Sir <persName type="to">Edward
                                    Thornton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 28,
                                1879</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 22d instant, in reply to one of this
                            Department of the 12th of August last, relative to encroachments by
                            Canadian fishermen within the jurisdiction of the United States, and to
                            express the gratification with which this Department has learned of the
                            prompt attention given to the subject by the Canadian Government. It is
                            hoped that the proposed action of the Canadian authorities will
                            supersede the necessity of any seizures or forfeitures on the part of
                            the United States.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
